'''Kozhuun''' ({{lang-tyv|кожуун}}) is the Tuvan term of an historical feudal [[administrative division]] known as a ''[[Banner (country subdivision)|banner]]''.
The term kozhuun is used today as a unit in the system of the [[administrative divisions of the Tuva Republic]] of [[Russia]].<ref name="Constitution">Constitution, Article 138.2a</ref> A typical [[federal subjects of Russia|federal subject]] of Russia is subdivided into [[raion]]s. ''Kozhuun'' is an ethnic name for a raion, used only in Tuva.
Tuva historically had nine kozhuun. Each kozhuun was divided into ''[[sum (country subdivision)|sumus]]'' which was then subdivided into ''arbans''.
List of historic kozhunn <!-- why this order? --> # [[Tozhu]] # [[Salchak]] # [[Oyunnar]] # [[Khemchik]] # [[Khaasuut]] # [[Shalyk]] # [[Nibazy]] # [[Daa-van and Choodu]] # [[Beezi]]
==See also== * [[sum (country subdivision)|sum]]
