== Episodes ==
=== Series 1 (2016) === Writing on the series began in February 2015 with [[principal photography]] commencing 29 June and wrapping in mid-August. The show was shot entirely on location due to no studio space being available in the UK. "But you can just be completely mobile now, and set up a video village anywhere", explained Ullman to Televisual magazine.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.televisual.com/blog-detail/Tracey-Ullman-one-of-a-kind_bid-847.html|title=Tracey Ullman: one of a kind|work=Televisual|publisher=Televisual.com|accessdate=23 August 2016}}</ref> A sketch featuring Ullman playing [[Cilla Black]] was filmed and scrapped after the star's untimely death in August 2015.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dailystar.co.uk/showbiz-tv/hot-tv/485796/BBC-Cilla-skit|title=BBC forced to axe bad taste Cilla skit|publisher=Daily Star|date=6 January 2016|accessdate=25 August 2016}}</ref> Audience screenings and recordings took place in September 2015 at [[Broadcasting House|BBC Radio Theatre]].<ref name=productiondata>{{cite web|url=https://www.comedy.co.uk/tv/the_tracey_ullman_show/details/|title=Tracey Ullman's Show production data|publisher=[[British Comedy Guide]]|date=|accessdate=1 November 2016}}</ref>
Series one received generally favourable reviews from critics.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/entertainment-arts-35292406|title=Tracey Ullman returns to TV 'on fighting form'|publisher=BBC News|date=12 January 2016|accessdate=24 October 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-3394843/Dame-Judi-thief-Merkel-sexpot-Tracey-s-hoot-CLAUDIA-CONNELL-reviews-weekend-s-TV.html|title=Dame Judi as a thief and Merkel as a sexpot! Tracey's still a hoot: CLAUDIA CONNELL reviews last weekend's TV|publisher=The Daily Mail|date=11 January 2016|accessdate=24 October 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/tv/reviews/a6806406.html|title=Headline: Tracey Ullman's Show, BBC1, TV review: Our Trace is on top with spot-on spoofs and social comment|publisher=The Independent|date=11 January 2016|accessdate=24 October 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/culture/tvandradio/bbc/12100120/Why-the-Tracey-Ullman-show-is-worth-watching-even-if-you-think-it-wont-be-funny.html|title=Why the Tracey Ullman show is worth watching – even if you think it won't be funny|publisher=The Telegraph|date=14 January 2016|accessdate=24 October 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bostonherald.com/entertainment/television/2016/10/tracey_ullman_takes_on_hilarious_new_roles_in_hbo_series|title=Tracey Ullman takes on hilarious new roles in HBO series|publisher=Boston Herald|date=28 October 2016|accessdate=29 October 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vogue.com/13497810/tracey-ullmans-show-hbo-review/|title=In Her New HBO Show, Tracey Ullman Proves She's an International Treasure|publisher=Vogue|date=28 October 2016|accessdate=29 October 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/tracey-ullmans-show-review-caustic-cause-for-celebration-1477600644|title=‘Tracey Ullman's Show’ Review: Caustic Cause for Celebration|publisher=The Wall Street Journal|date=27 October 2016|accessdate=29 October 2016}}</ref> [[Metacritic]] rated the series 70/100 based on 7 reviews.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.metacritic.com/tv/tracey-ullmans-show|title=Tracey Ullman's Show|work=[[Metacritic]]|accessdate=29 October 2016}}</ref> Several critics chided the BBC's decision to give the show a 'graveyard' time slot. Ullman contended that she didn't believe there was "appointment TV" anymore, and that people could watch whenever they wanted on catch up.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.express.co.uk/showbiz/tv-radio/635007/Comedian-Tracey-Ullman-Angela-Merkel-the-Duchess-of-Conrwall-Maggie-Smith|title='Such a thrill':Comedian Tracey Ullman returns with a new show on BBC|publisher=Daily Express|date=17 January 2016|accessdate=25 August 2016}}</ref>
